title: Google\Cloud\AIPlatform\V1\Trial
name: Trial
description:
A message representing a Trial. A Trial contains a unique set of Parameters that has been or will be evaluated, along with the objective metrics got by running the Trial.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.Trial

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Output only. Resource name of the Trial assigned by the service.

params.name: data.id
params.description: Output only. The identifier of the Trial assigned by the service.

params.name: data.state
params.description: Output only. The detailed state of the Trial.

params.name: data.parameters
params.description: Output only. The parameters of the Trial.

params.name: data.final_measurement
params.description: Output only. The final measurement containing the objective value.

params.name: data.measurements
params.description: Output only. A list of measurements that are strictly lexicographically ordered by their induced tuples (steps, elapsed_duration). These are used for early stopping computations.

params.name: data.start_time
params.description: Output only. Time when the Trial was started.

params.name: data.end_time
params.description: Output only. Time when the Trial's status changed to SUCCEEDED or INFEASIBLE.

params.name: data.client_id
params.description: Output only. The identifier of the client that originally requested this Trial. Each client is identified by a unique client_id. When a client asks for a suggestion, Vertex AI Vizier will assign it a Trial. The client should evaluate the Trial, complete it, and report back to Vertex AI Vizier. If suggestion is asked again by same client_id before the Trial is completed, the same Trial will be returned. Multiple clients with different client_ids can ask for suggestions simultaneously, each of them will get their own Trial.

params.name: data.infeasible_reason
params.description: Output only. A human readable string describing why the Trial is infeasible. This is set only if Trial state is INFEASIBLE.

params.name: data.custom_job
params.description: Output only. The CustomJob name linked to the Trial. It's set for a HyperparameterTuningJob's Trial.

params.name: data.web_access_uris
params.description: Output only. URIs for accessing interactive shells (one URI for each training node). Only available if this trial is part of a [HyperparameterTuningJob][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.HyperparameterTuningJob] and the job's [trial_job_spec.enable_web_access][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.CustomJobSpec.enable_web_access] field is true. The keys are names of each node used for the trial; for example, workerpool0-0 for the primary node, workerpool1-0 for the first node in the second worker pool, and workerpool1-1 for the second node in the second worker pool. The values are the URIs for each node's interactive shell.
